{
  "texts": [
    "Other platforms, such as HuggingFace, Papers with Code, the UCI ML Repository, and OpenML, also facilitate benchmarking (typically without monetary components) by providing infrastructure to host data, share models, and track performance on public leaderboards.",
    "As such, the line between these categories can blur.",
    "Despite the success of benchmarking in other fields, its application in gambling studies remains nascent, with no formal benchmark datasets for player risk detection.",
    "The closest example is research stemming from The Transparency Project foot_6, which made several datasets publicly available.",
    "The bwin dataset, in particular, functioned as a de facto benchmark for researchers interested in player risk detection."
  ]
}